result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 8:22 Defendant Benjamin L Digangi in court with attorney James L. McFarland.  Derek Dominguez appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Dismissed & Read-in to 13CF407.
Jury trial - 12 person on December 17, 2014 at 08:15 am.

1:18 Defendant Benjamin L Digangi in court, in custody.   Derek Dominguez appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Jordan Lubeck is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Dominguez. He is a police officer with the Wisconsin Rapids Police Department. On 7/20/14 he arrested defendant on a warrant in the City of Wisconsin Rapids. He recognized defendant from previous contacts. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom. He was transported to the Wood County Jail. A glass pipe fell out of his shoe when being searched in the jail. The pipe had burnt residue that appeared to be marijuana. 
Attorney Dominguez asks Court to take judical notice of bond in Wood County case 13CF407. Court takes judicial notice.
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Bound over for further proceedings. Court enters not guilty plea to both counts. Bond is continued.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 24, 2014 at 10:00 am.
Preliminary hearing and Arraignment on September 30, 2014 at 01:15 pm.
9:24 Defendant Benjamin L Digangi in court.  Derek Dominguez appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Count 1 bound over for preliminary hearing. Not guilty plea by Court to Count 2.
